commit.message:
Ensured helper mnethods were available in command with configs

This patch adds delegate methods to a command's configuration object to
expose any helper methods that were defined in the command class.

Fixed a bug caused by inheriting from a configuration

Previously, if you subclassed a configuration and added new options,
these new options would appear in the superclass.  To avoid this issue
we now clone the arrays that contain the options lists.
Avoid re-definition of accessors.

Added a new exception to distinguish between command and code errors

This CL adds the CommandArgumentError to distinguish when a command
failed to run due to bad input from when a call inside the command
failed.
Added support for instance defaults to configuration construction.
Added an additional proxy class test

Added a helper class for proxying calls to a member object.

This patch adds a new mixin for proxying calls to one or more objects
referenced by instance variables.  Any call that isn't handled by one
of the proxy objects will raise the standard NoMethodError.

Improved option handling for configurations.

This patch provides two features for configurations:
1. A specific storage name can now be used to override using the long
name as the name of the variable holding the computed values.
2. Option handlers may now have optional parameters.
Better help messages for commands.
Added support for a configuration finalizer.

Small bug fixes and new functionality.

Added some string coloring functions.
Added an enum type checking function.
Fixed a couple of warnings.
Fixed an issue with handling of array arguments.
Fixed a bug introduced by a merge and fixed handling of auto options in Configuration.
Bug fixes for commands and configuration.
Bumped the sub-minor version number for development.

Small updates to support files.

* Updated the gemfile with additional info.
* Added a TODO item for a bug.
* Removed the rubygem-tasks gem due to it being broken.
Fixed some printing and moved an accessor definition.
Small edit to the TODO file.
Finished updating code for Ruby 2.4
Work on modernizing the visitor and configuration classes.
Updated the Rakefile.
Working on modernizing the library.
A better fix for an uninitialized value bug.
Fixed warning issued by the testing infrastructure.
Moved the `match` function into the Filigree namespace.
Fixed bug in documentation.
Formatting for file header.
Added more functionality to visitable objects.
Fixed an issue with short circuiting.
Modified the behavior of the visitor class to indicate if a match is found.
